00:38:28,760 --> 00:38:30,930
and a fairytale book.

516
00:38:30,930 --> 00:38:35,060
That day, right here,

517
00:38:35,980 --> 00:38:40,650
we had a really wonderful afternoon.

518
00:38:41,880 --> 00:38:45,820
I still remember that afternoon. She kept telling me about

519
00:38:45,820 --> 00:38:48,350
a fairytale about a little prince.

520
00:38:49,370 --> 00:38:51,270
Twenty years later,

521
00:38:52,940 --> 00:38:57,190
fate allowed us to meet again.

522
00:38:58,610 --> 00:39:01,420
I brought her to this lawn again.

523
00:39:01,420 --> 00:39:04,360
I asked her uneasily...

524
00:39:04,910 --> 00:39:07,080
"Do you still remember me?"

525
00:39:07,080 --> 00:39:10,450
Do you know how much I wanted to hear her say,

526
00:39:10,450 --> 00:39:12,170
"I remember"?

527
00:39:13,750 --> 00:39:16,090
But she told me,

528
00:39:19,070 --> 00:39:23,320
"I only remember a black ladybug."

529
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:35,000
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

530
00:39:35,740 --> 00:39:38,450
If I told you earlier, then you wouldn't be surprised.

531
00:39:47,410 --> 00:39:51,420
But I was only 5 years old back then, how would I remember?

532
00:39:55,760 --> 00:40:01,430
Everything today... feels like a dream.

533
00:40:07,510 --> 00:40:09,970
It is like a dream.

534
00:40:15,410 --> 00:40:19,100
We used 20 years of time

535
00:40:19,100 --> 00:40:23,090
to walk out of a dream and get to each other's side.

536
00:40:23,090 --> 00:40:27,580
We met. Then I fell in love with her.

537
00:40:29,460 --> 00:40:31,610
Today,

538
00:40:36,670 --> 00:40:38,950
